==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*grimmaz'', from Indo-European ''*ghrem-'' ‘to thunder’.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''grim'', Old High German ''grim'' (German [[grimm]]), Old Norse [[grimmr]] (Danish ''grim''); and with Greek [[χρεμίζω]], Old Church Slavonic [[грьмѣти]] (Russian [[греметь]]), Latvian [[gremt]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/grɪm/}}

===Adjective===
'''grim'''
# [[fierce]], [[severe]], [[terrible]]

